<subSubSection id="70E51A85FF812569FF4BADFEAEF8CDBD" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="3840490EFF812569FF4BADFEAE47CFC1" blockId="30.[151,1437,1577,2037]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1437,152,683]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFF812556FF4BADFEAD95C98A" bold="true" box="[199,418,1685,1712]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Whole fly as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FDB0ADFDAEACC98A" box="[572,667,1686,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 190</figureCitation>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FC85ADFDAF52C98A" box="[777,869,1686,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 191</figureCitation>
largely lacking fine microtrichia (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FB6DADFDA975C98A" box="[1249,1346,1686,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 192</figureCitation>
). Cheek with 2 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FEA6ADB5ADBDC9C2" box="[298,394,1758,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 193</figureCitation>
, the labella with only a few short spinules below. Thorax brown, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these and mesopleuron bare (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FD69AC69AF70C826" box="[741,839,1794,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 194</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown with hairs a little longer at rear of T6, and venter grayish brown, with numerous long hairs on segments 3–6 (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FD0BAC21AEDDC85E" box="[647,746,1865,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 190–196" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionTargetBox="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 195</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FC3AAC21A864C85E" box="[950,1107,1865,1892]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 190–196" captionStart-1="FIGURES 197–200" captionStartId-0="32.[151,264,1977,2002]" captionStartId-1="33.[151,264,1425,1450]" captionTargetBox-0="[174,1403,197,1932]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1416,707,1386]" captionTargetId-0="figure@32.[164,1423,181,1951]" captionTargetId-1="figure@33.[151,1436,705,1400]" captionTargetPageId-0="32" captionTargetPageId-1="33" captionText-0="FIGURES 190–196. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 190, whole fly; 191, frons; 192, detail of frons; 193, postpedicel, palp and proboscis; 194, side of thorax; 195, side of abdomen; 196, left face of epandrium and anal tube. Scale bars 20 μm." captionText-1="FIGURES 197–200. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 197, left hypandrial lobe; 198, right face of hypandrium; 199, front tarsus; 200, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573422" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573424" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3573422/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3573424/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 195–198</figureCitation>
. The tapered left hypandrium lobe (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FF5BAC05AD01C8B2" box="[215,310,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 197–200" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1425,1450]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,707,1386]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,705,1400]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 197–200. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 197, left hypandrial lobe; 198, right face of hypandrium; 199, front tarsus; 200, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573424/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 197</figureCitation>
) has microtrichia (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FD87AC05AE59C8B2" box="[523,622,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 197–200" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1425,1450]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,707,1386]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,705,1400]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 197–200. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 197, left hypandrial lobe; 198, right face of hypandrium; 199, front tarsus; 200, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573424/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 197</figureCitation>
). Legs dusky yellow to yellow. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FBD1AC05A88AC8B2" box="[1117,1213,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 197–200" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1425,1450]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,707,1386]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,705,1400]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 197–200. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 197, left hypandrial lobe; 198, right face of hypandrium; 199, front tarsus; 200, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573424/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 199</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 longer than 4. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.57 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur clearly longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFF812556FAA2ACDDA9A6C8EA" box="[1326,1425,1974,2000]" captionStart="FIGURES 197–200" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1425,1450]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,707,1386]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,705,1400]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 197–200. Megaselia ledzona n. sp. male. 197, left hypandrial lobe; 198, right face of hypandrium; 199, front tarsus; 200, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573424/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 200</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with a dozen moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFBE2569FE02ABF2ADC4CF89" box="[398,499,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.48" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="1.48">1.48 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.36. Costal ratios 3.51: 1.37: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFBE2569FAE7ABF2ACF4CFED" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 hair 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFBE2569FE18ABD6ADCECFED" box="[404,505,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
long. With 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFBE2569FB28ABD6A93DCFED" box="[1188,1290,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale yellowish.
</paragraph>
